    public class MessageEvent
extends CatalysEventObject
implements IMessageEvent
    Default implementation of an IMessageEvent.

    This implementation is based on our standard CatalysEventObject.

      • isPossiblyStored

        public boolean isPossiblyStored()
        Description copied from interface: IMessageEvent
        The possiblyStored attribute indicates that a reference to this event object may be stored somewhere. This can be used to detect whether the object can be reused or not. Message events can only be reused if this attribute is false.

        Default is false.

        Specified by:
        isPossiblyStored in interface IMessageEvent
        Returns:
        True if a reference to this message event may be stored somewhere.
